about keeping Sofía's secret?

14:36.383 --> 14:37.886
- What?
No.

14:37.986 --> 14:40.249
Nah, I think it's just,
when you really open your eyes,

14:40.349 --> 14:43.293
you realise
everything's very dirty.

14:43.393 --> 14:45.496
You know, we live in a dirty,
dirty world, and you and I

14:45.596 --> 14:46.738
are just trying to clean it up,
and, oh, my God,

14:46.838 --> 14:48.020
I think I can still hear
that watch ticking.

14:48.120 --> 14:49.782
- It's insanely loud.
- Right?

14:49.882 --> 14:51.905
- And that's the crazy thing
about diphtheria.

14:52.005 --> 14:53.427
It's super infectious.

14:53.527 --> 14:56.151
- Yeah, yeah.
- Kind of like Blink-182.

14:56.251 --> 14:58.114
- [laughs]

14:58.214 --> 15:00.717
That's hilarious.
We're both so into Blink.

15:00.817 --> 15:03.000
- Yeah, we get it.

15:03.100 --> 15:04.883
- You know, we--we should
do this again sometime

15:04.983 --> 15:07.206
but like a--a real date,
you know,

15:07.306 --> 15:08.688
in a--in a sister-free
environment.

15:08.788 --> 15:10.731
- And I am a lock
for maid of honour.

15:10.831 --> 15:12.173
- Okay.
Be cool.

15:12.273 --> 15:13.335
- That'd be fun.

15:13.435 --> 15:15.177
I'd love to do something
by the water.

15:15.277 --> 15:17.340
I feel like I've barely seen
the bay since I moved here.

15:17.440 --> 15:18.862
- Oh, they say the best way
to take in the bay

15:18.962 --> 15:21.466
is--is by boat,
and I have a boat.

15:21.566 --> 15:23.188
- I pretty much grew up
on a boat.

15:23.288 --> 15:24.951
- What?
- Yeah.

15:25.051 --> 15:26.673
- Ah! Oh, my God.
[cell phone chimes]

15:26.773 --> 15:28.796
Look, I just got a match
on Raya.

15:28.896 --> 15:30.038
I'm gonna go.

15:30.138 --> 15:32.140
- Oh, no.
Bye.

15:33.743 --> 15:36.807
- So should we set it up
for this Saturday?

15:36.907 --> 15:38.810
- For what?

15:38.910 --> 15:40.773
- Sailing.
You two.

15:40.873 --> 15:42.295
On a boat.
'Cause of me.

15:42.395 --> 15:44.137
- It's gonna be so fun.

15:44.237 --> 15:45.739
Okay, you must have heard that,
right?

15:45.839 --> 15:46.821
It's like a woodpecker.

15:46.921 --> 15:48.583
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Do it again.

15:48.683 --> 15:51.748
- Here's one, the book's a hit,
it'll lead to more jobs.

15:51.848 --> 15:54.191
- So another sock
for the keep quiet pile.

15:54.291 --> 15:56.234
- And I mean, Sofía lied,

15:56.334 --> 15:58.717
but it's not like she
committed a crime

15:58.817 --> 16:01.121
that we know of.

16:01.221 --> 16:03.844
- We'll call this Sofía
not a murderer yet.

16:03.944 --> 16:06.168
- [chuckles]

16:06.268 --> 16:07.810
Well, still just one sock

16:07.910 --> 16:10.333
in the expose
Sofía's secret pile.

16:10.433 --> 16:12.336
- Seeing it laid out like this,
I feel better.

16:12.436 --> 16:13.778
I do.
- Yeah, it's the right move.

16:13.878 --> 16:16.061
- Yeah.
- More cleaning?

16:16.161 --> 16:18.425
- Oh, no, sweetie.

16:18.525 --> 16:21.269
This is kind of
a complicated grown-up thing.

16:21.369 --> 16:23.151
- We had to make a decision,

16:23.251 --> 16:26.756
so we decided to separate
baby sock piles into two.

16:26.856 --> 16:28.398
And for every reason
we decided one way,

16:28.498 --> 16:30.201
we'd put a sock in this pile,

16:30.301 --> 16:31.923
and for the other way,
that pile.

16:32.023 --> 16:33.085
- What's that one
by itself for?

16:33.185 --> 16:35.929
- Oh, this one's just a--

16:36.029 --> 16:37.651
well, it's kind of 'cause Daddy
felt guilty

16:37.751 --> 16:42.017
about not being able
to tell 100% of the truth.

16:42.117 --> 16:45.422
- You mean lying.
- Um...

16:45.522 --> 16:49.027
well, I wouldn't say--
I didn't say lying

16:49.127 --> 16:52.672
because it's not
technically lying.

16:52.772 --> 16:55.195
But if you--I guess if you look
at the definition of--

16:55.295 --> 16:58.360
- Okay, um, Camila,
can you give us a minute?

16:58.460 --> 17:02.085
And please stop silently
judging us.

17:02.185 --> 17:04.829
Thank you.
- [sighs]

17:09.675 --> 17:12.359
- Disappointing our daughter.
- Yeah.

17:15.323 --> 17:17.907
[cell phone ringing]

17:18.007 --> 17:19.309
- It's my agent.

17:19.409 --> 17:20.470
- Remember, we did
the right thing.

17:20.570 --> 17:22.573
- Right.

17:23.414 --> 17:25.758
Amanda, what's going on?

17:25.858 --> 17:27.240
- An anonymous source
leaked some info

17:27.340 --> 17:28.842
about Sofía Salazar.

17:28.942 --> 17:32.327
She made up
her rags-to-riches story.

17:32.427 --> 17:35.411
- What?
- She lied to us, Tom,

17:35.511 --> 17:37.534
and now it looks like
the book's not coming out.

17:37.634 --> 17:40.458
- Oh, my--what are you
talking--that's crazy.

17:40.558 --> 17:42.501
That's crazy.
- Okay, pull it back, honey.

17:42.601 --> 17:43.662
- Okay.

17:43.762 --> 17:45.946
- So what are we
gonna sell next?

17:46.046 --> 17:48.429
- There's always my novel.

17:48.529 --> 17:50.672
- Ooh, a novel.
What's it about?

17:50.772 --> 17:52.475
- You've already read
half of it.

17:52.575 --> 17:54.117
Remember, it's about my family.

17:54.217 --> 17:55.919
Three siblings, different
levels of financial success.

17:56.019 --> 17:57.562
- Sounds great.

17:57.662 --> 18:00.045
Too bad you wasted your time
on Sofía's book.

18:00.145 --> 18:01.527
- You talked me into it.

18:01.627 --> 18:03.049
- Who can remember
who did what?

18:03.149 --> 18:05.493
You just get back at it,
Tommy boy.

18:05.593 --> 18:07.295
- [sighs]

18:07.395 --> 18:09.018
Well, back to square one.

18:09.118 --> 18:10.460
- Yeah, we got nothing

18:10.560 --> 18:12.943
without the victim's
phone records.

18:13.043 --> 18:15.266
Oh, you meant financially.
